1
00:00:00,630 --> 00:00:04,740
Characters, actions, places, occupations,

2
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:09,730
and events in this series are fictional
and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:09,790 --> 00:00:14,410
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:16,860
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:17,460 --> 00:00:20,940
You’ve been acting contradictory lately.

6
00:00:22,260 --> 00:00:23,500
You said you don’t like me.

7
00:00:24,890 --> 00:00:25,420
Yeah.

8
00:00:27,140 --> 00:00:27,980
I like you.

9
00:00:28,770 --> 00:00:31,140
With Jira, for example.
If he doesn’t reciprocate your feelings,

10
00:00:31,540 --> 00:00:32,740
just find someone else.

11
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,790
He said he’d draw me.

12
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:36,940
He’s going to show me
my painting tomorrow.

13
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:39,380
If you think I’m such an asshole,

14
00:00:40,980 --> 00:00:42,170
will you leave me?

15
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:43,660
What do you mean?

16
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:46,860
Should we just start dating?

17
00:02:23,730 --> 00:02:25,540
Don’t you just get deja vu?

18
00:02:26,610 --> 00:02:27,100
What?

19
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,500
Well, you were waiting for me
here as well last time.

20
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:32,570
Oh.

21
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:34,060
I did.

22
00:02:36,370 --> 00:02:37,820
How do you want me to look at it?

23
00:02:39,790 --> 00:02:41,120
Look at it as a curator.

24
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:44,180
If it were you, which of these paintings
would you include in your gallery?

25
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:56,100
I like this one.

26
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:58,020
Why?

27
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,140
It’s acrylic.

28
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,780
It feels feisty.

29
00:03:05,570 --> 00:03:09,900
Fits well with this generation that
feels aggressively about everything.

30
00:03:10,370 --> 00:03:16,700
It’s like you want this man to be free
from his sadness and messiness.

31
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,980
You mentioned my painting.

32
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,060
Are you really done with it?

33
00:03:26,370 --> 00:03:26,890
Yeah.

34
00:03:29,260 --> 00:03:32,340
Should we find somewhere to take a look?

35
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:33,460
Okay.

36
00:03:33,930 --> 00:03:34,900
Let me help.

37
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:40,940
On the other hand,

38
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:44,620
I like this painting of Koh.

39
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:48,260
You know I like classical paintings.

40
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:52,260
I’m actually quite in awe that
you can paint death in such an erotic way.

41
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:54,660
What I’m trying to say is

42
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:58,820
I can say whatever I want to make
each piece sound amazing.

43
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:00,900
But you’re the artist.

44
00:04:01,870 --> 00:04:04,820
You have to choose for yourself
which painting you like.

45
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,460
Which one is mine?

46
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:25,940
The black one.

47
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:29,340
I’ll take a look right away.

48
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,020
Can you take a look at it later?

49
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:34,420
I…

50
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:37,100
I don’t know if you’d like it.

51
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:41,060
But it just felt so right
when I was painting it.

52
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,620
If it’s your painting, there’s no way
I wouldn’t like it.

53
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,740
Why? Do you think it’s bad?

54
00:04:59,810 --> 00:05:00,300
Uh…

55
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:02,750
Are you alright?

56
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,500
Pheem.

57
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:18,740
Hmm?

58
00:05:22,470 --> 00:05:23,900
I’ve been thinking…

59
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:29,020
that we’re better off as friends.

60
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,180
I really like you.

61
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,260
I just don’t want us to fall out.

62
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:58,980
Okay.

63
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:02,500
Well…

64
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,900
I knew…

65
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,220
this day would come.

66
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:15,060
I just didn’t expect it to be so soon.

67
00:06:22,710 --> 00:06:24,700
Jira, can I ask?

68
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,980
Am I not good enough?

69
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:30,340
What did I do wrong? Just tell me.

70
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:31,410
No.

71
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:33,420
You’re good.

72
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,530
You’re actually very good.

73
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:38,620
Okay, then.

74
00:06:40,380 --> 00:06:42,210
Do you like the painting you did of me?

75
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,500
Yes.

76
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,860
But you like the other one more…

77
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:50,580
Do I understand that right?

78
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,790
Can I take a look at Koh’s painting?

79
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:09,980
Just show me.

80
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,340
I need something to help me move on.

81
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:48,940
Shit.

82
00:07:59,330 --> 00:07:59,900
Crap.

83
00:08:01,570 --> 00:08:02,100
Shit.

84
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,500
Crap, I can’t—
I can’t hold a candle to that.

85
00:08:16,150 --> 00:08:17,580
Shit, this hurts as hell.

86
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:20,620
I’m sorry.

87
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:22,100
Oh, no.

88
00:08:23,580 --> 00:08:24,980
Don’t apologize to me like that.

89
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:30,860
I freaking hate it when people apologize
because they can’t love you.

90
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:32,780
So don’t do that to me.

91
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,020
It’s too brutal for me.

92
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,780
But I really want to apologize.

93
00:08:47,090 --> 00:08:47,860
Okay.

94
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:50,580
Since you’ve made your decision,

95
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:53,220
let me warn you.

96
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,980
One day, you will be tired of Koh.

97
00:08:58,250 --> 00:08:58,860
Trust me.

98
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:04,070
Because Koh is no more than a capitalist.

99
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,940
He loves you only as long as
you’re useful to him.

100
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:14,420
The only way you can be happy with him
is by constantly proving your worth.

101
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:18,420
I know.

102
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,980
But I’ve made up my mind.

103
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:34,940
Yeah.

104
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:36,260
Come to think about it,

105
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,140
you’re special.

106
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:41,180
Maybe you can do it.

107
00:09:43,660 --> 00:09:44,330
I’m going home.

108
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:51,740
Pheem.

109
00:09:52,590 --> 00:09:53,020
Pheem.

110
00:09:53,660 --> 00:09:54,100
Pheem.

111
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:57,300
What?

112
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,740
I want you to have this.

113
00:10:02,070 --> 00:10:03,380
I can’t afford it.

114
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:07,420
I don’t expect you to buy it.

115
00:10:08,630 --> 00:10:09,580
I just want to give it to you.

116
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:13,820
Do whatever you want with it.

117
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:17,420
If you don’t see any value in it,

118
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,100
you can just throw it away.

119
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,300
Hey, flame lily.

120
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,460
You’re here to remind me
not to be a bitch.

121
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:21,330
That’s your job.

122
00:12:13,010 --> 00:12:13,630
Hey.

123
00:12:15,450 --> 00:12:16,140
Tonight…

124
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:19,660
Can I come over to your place?

125
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,060
Are you alright?

126
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:25,700
Just frustrated.

127
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:28,300
So I want to see you.

128
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:31,420
Okay. Just wait over there.

129
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:32,300
I’ll pick you up.

130
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:34,140
It’s alright.

131
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,140
I’ll get there myself.

132
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:39,020
You don’t have to come
all the way here and back.

133
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,620
I don’t want you to waste your time
hailing a ride.

134
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:43,150
I want to take care of you.

135
00:12:43,660 --> 00:12:45,420
(You can just sit back and
relax in my car.)

136
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:47,180
Ew. How awful.

137
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:48,420
(Alright.)

138
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,020
(If you insist.)

139
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:51,650
Okay.

140
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:24,010
KOH

141
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,500
(Hello.)

142
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:28,810
(I’m downstairs.)

143
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,610
(Can you look down here
from the balcony?)

144
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:42,620
Why are you posing?

145
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,690
Wait there.

146
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,220
I’ll come up to you.

147
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:07,500
Hey.

148
00:14:08,210 --> 00:14:10,060
Aren’t I supposed to sleep over
at your place

149
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,100
or do you plan to stay over at mine?

150
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,590
Let’s stay here.

151
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:19,700
Don’t.

152
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:23,580
You done painting?

153
00:14:25,940 --> 00:14:26,540
Which one?

154
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:27,740
Both.

155
00:14:29,430 --> 00:14:30,620
I finished the rose painting.

156
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:33,820
But I haven’t gotten to the other one
since I can’t get in the mood to paint.

157
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:38,660
Let me buy your rose painting.

158
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:39,940
How much would you sell it for?

159
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,580
Same price as the previous one.

160
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:48,060
Okay.

161
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,500
I’ll wire you the money.

162
00:14:53,820 --> 00:14:57,020
I’m giving you 10% more, though,

163
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,980
so your work increases in value.

164
00:15:01,530 --> 00:15:02,620
Do you want to see it first?

165
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:06,910
Later.

166
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:09,220
I have an experiment I’d like to try.

167
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:11,740
What experiment?

168
00:15:12,290 --> 00:15:13,580
It wouldn’t be a surprise if I told you.

169
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:26,340
-What are you doing?
-Hmm?

170
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:28,180
Oh.

171
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:32,620
I just want to take photos of
your balcony as a keepsake.

172
00:15:33,690 --> 00:15:36,620
Can you take a photo in the same
perspective as your painting?

173
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,020
Lay down.

174
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:53,610
All done.

175
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:05,100
Why are you so nice today?

176
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,210
You let me do whatever I want.

177
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:09,020
It’s the honeymoon phase.

178
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:11,020
It’ll be over soon.

179
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:14,980
What are we, dating?

180
00:16:18,830 --> 00:16:19,900
Aren’t we?

181
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:30,070
What’s this flower?

182
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:31,460
I’ve never seen it before.

183
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:39,620
Flame lily.

184
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,930
Strange name.

185
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:52,220
Did you know that it takes a lot of
energy for flowers to bloom?

186
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,380
That’s why I like flowers.

187
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:57,780
It shows a kind of struggle,

188
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:01,860
of death…

189
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:07,500
and beauty.

190
00:17:09,869 --> 00:17:11,020
Depends on who’s looking at it.

191
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:18,859
To spend my life with it,
taking care of it,

192
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:21,260
until it blossoms,

193
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:22,859
really inspires me.

194
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:25,420
How about this?

195
00:17:26,099 --> 00:17:28,270
Move it to my balcony.

196
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:33,260
I bet it’ll be competing to blossom.

197
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:36,870
Which direction does your balcony face?

198
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:38,270
Hmm…

199
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:40,220
West.

200
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:42,460
There are sunlights
in the afternoon and evening.

201
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:47,300
We can try and see if it works.

202
00:17:49,620 --> 00:17:50,810
Come and take care of it.

203
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,100
Move in with me.

204
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:56,460
Are you using the flowers
as an excuse to ask?

205
00:17:58,220 --> 00:17:58,890
You could say that.

206
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:30,390
Oh?

207
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,550
Why is it wilting already?

208
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:35,860
We’ll see if you’ll survive.

209
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:37,540
Hold on, dear.

210
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,350
I’ll make sure you’re well fed.

211
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:51,050
You’ll be staying here with Mr. Koh.

212
00:18:51,070 --> 00:18:53,190
Bloom soon, alright?

213
00:18:54,610 --> 00:18:55,300
You like that?

214
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:04,580
I’ll place it here.

215
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:05,140
Okay.

216
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:11,660
Let me get back to this.

217
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:12,900
I was working on it.

218
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:15,420
Feel free to use the shower if you want.

219
00:19:15,890 --> 00:19:16,380
Umm.

220
00:19:29,490 --> 00:19:30,140
Hey.

221
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:33,170
Just find something to do.

222
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:34,260
You’re making me blush.

223
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,140
I won’t finish this otherwise.

224
00:19:37,490 --> 00:19:38,860
But I just want to watch.

225
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,660
I’m curious about it.

226
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:42,370
I don’t get to see this every day,
you know?

227
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,420
I do this all the time.

228
00:19:44,930 --> 00:19:46,310
You’ll be sick of it soon.

229
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:47,220
Well…

230
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,540
Let me get familiar with this sight.

231
00:19:59,180 --> 00:19:59,700
Hey.

232
00:20:00,110 --> 00:20:00,590
Hmm?

233
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,750
Do you still need this?

234
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:03,620
Umm.

235
00:20:06,620 --> 00:20:07,220
And this?

236
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,540
-No.
-Okay.

237
00:20:20,230 --> 00:20:21,020
And these two?

238
00:20:23,450 --> 00:20:24,820
I don’t need them both.

239
00:20:25,370 --> 00:20:26,340
What do you want them for?

240
00:20:27,270 --> 00:20:28,980
Just keep being your tech bro self.

241
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,700
I’m just making art.

242
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:39,860
What’s with you and
computers and technology?

243
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:41,750
I’m just following the world’s trends.

244
00:20:42,410 --> 00:20:43,790
Tech is the new art.

245
00:20:50,060 --> 00:20:50,660
Hey!

246
00:20:51,810 --> 00:20:53,300
Do you hate them that much?

247
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:55,540
Oh, no…

248
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:59,420
They’re broken, ruined, and destroyed.

249
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:00,860
I don’t hate them.

250
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:03,380
I’m just doing what you said.

251
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:04,980
Tech is the new art.

252
00:21:09,430 --> 00:21:11,020
Are you sure you don’t hate them?

253
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:15,220
These two fields are always intertwined,
you know?

254
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,660
Think of Da Vinci.

255
00:21:18,230 --> 00:21:19,820
He was talented in many disciplines.

256
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:24,380
And he used his knowledge in optics
to paint The Last Supper.

257
00:21:25,070 --> 00:21:27,110
The reason there are films today

258
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:30,180
is because there was an invention
called a movie camera.

259
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,230
And now it’s AI’s turn.

260
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:33,860
That’s not true.

261
00:21:34,690 --> 00:21:39,270
Are you saying that an AI
generating images is making art?

262
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,140
All AI does is mix up a bunch of
other people’s art

263
00:21:42,150 --> 00:21:43,500
to generate what you want.

264
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:44,660
It’s awful.

265
00:21:45,050 --> 00:21:46,620
It’s practically stealing.

266
00:21:47,060 --> 00:21:48,860
You’re totally devaluing my work.

267
00:21:50,420 --> 00:21:51,300
Aren’t I right, though?

268
00:21:53,230 --> 00:21:55,060
I don’t think it’s all that different
from traditional art.

269
00:21:55,450 --> 00:21:56,780
You’re an artist.

270
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:59,620
You need to study other people’s art
and process it.

271
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:03,300
Take this and that from everybody
to make your own.

272
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:06,660
You need references
when you paint me, don’t you?

273
00:22:06,980 --> 00:22:08,950
Art can be taught,

274
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:11,570
and not superficially.

275
00:22:12,150 --> 00:22:14,860
It has to go through the process
of thinking, analyzing,

276
00:22:15,140 --> 00:22:19,540
and choosing an inspiration
to make one piece of art.

277
00:22:20,590 --> 00:22:22,820
Then I don’t think AI is
