00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:49,020
I just want you to know what kind
of things the AI I built is capable of.

561
00:41:49,350 --> 00:41:52,420
So I feed the paintings I bought
from you to AI to study.

562
00:41:52,900 --> 00:41:55,220
Draw a nude of a man lying on a balcony,

563
00:41:56,260 --> 00:41:58,940
based on the painting
The Roses of Heliogabalus,

564
00:41:59,150 --> 00:42:02,980
and the recently added preset
in Jira’s style.

565
00:42:04,060 --> 00:42:05,540
You’ll see something soon.

566
00:42:08,970 --> 00:42:11,350
Let me compare it to your painting.

567
00:42:12,710 --> 00:42:13,460
Hey.

568
00:42:14,670 --> 00:42:15,300
What’s wrong?

569
00:42:20,180 --> 00:42:21,140
Calm down.

570
00:42:23,010 --> 00:42:26,100
When it’s done generating,
we’ll see it together.

571
00:42:29,190 --> 00:42:30,260
Trust me.

572
00:43:03,870 --> 00:43:04,830
Yes! See?

573
00:43:05,530 --> 00:43:06,290
We made it!

574
00:43:07,330 --> 00:43:11,860
This will definitely break the record as
the most expensive software ever sold.

575
00:43:12,410 --> 00:43:13,330
What do you think?

576
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:38,660
Do you remember when you first saw
my painting at my place?

577
00:43:42,620 --> 00:43:44,810
My painting moved you

578
00:43:47,230 --> 00:43:48,660
to the point where you had to ask me

579
00:43:51,140 --> 00:43:52,140
how I did it.

580
00:43:56,110 --> 00:43:57,860
Every time I paint you,

581
00:44:00,420 --> 00:44:01,740
it means so much to me.

582
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,290
It feels alive

583
00:44:05,540 --> 00:44:09,780
because I paint it based on
who you are at the time.

584
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:14,500
That’s the bond between an artist

585
00:44:15,870 --> 00:44:16,620
and his model.

586
00:44:17,580 --> 00:44:19,180
But this fucking AI-generated image…

587
00:44:20,450 --> 00:44:21,180
is deformed,

588
00:44:22,250 --> 00:44:23,540
and a cheap copy of my work.

589
00:44:23,750 --> 00:44:24,460
Hey.

590
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:26,630
Take another look.

591
00:44:28,470 --> 00:44:30,470
This could make our lives easier.

592
00:44:31,660 --> 00:44:34,260
(This is the design based on the preset.)

593
00:44:34,750 --> 00:44:35,940
(This past month,)

594
00:44:36,730 --> 00:44:39,470
(Library has been using my AI.)

595
00:44:39,740 --> 00:44:41,260
The silhouette seems slick.

596
00:44:41,370 --> 00:44:44,430
But I can’t see how it would look
on an actual model.

597
00:44:45,090 --> 00:44:47,610
(Thames came in to talk
to the AI once a week,)

598
00:44:48,250 --> 00:44:49,580
(just like you were doing just now.)

599
00:44:50,260 --> 00:44:51,030
I don’t believe you.

600
00:44:52,980 --> 00:44:54,980
Thames wouldn’t do something so stupid.

601
00:44:55,160 --> 00:44:56,620
Thames loves my AI.

602
00:44:58,160 --> 00:45:01,900
Everything depends on your tastes
and your decisions, right?

603
00:45:02,310 --> 00:45:04,790
If, one day, Thames’ taste
became obsolete,

604
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:08,940
we can hire new designers,
or some influencers with good taste,

605
00:45:08,960 --> 00:45:11,580
for an hour to run the system.

606
00:45:13,150 --> 00:45:14,970
Pandora's box is already opened.

607
00:45:15,980 --> 00:45:17,190
We can’t stop it.

608
00:45:18,720 --> 00:45:21,210
It’s all about how we can coexist
with it now.

609
00:45:24,560 --> 00:45:25,510
I understand you now.

610
00:45:28,390 --> 00:45:29,590
Delete this fucking image.

611
00:45:29,800 --> 00:45:30,360
Hey.

612
00:45:31,330 --> 00:45:32,860
I didn’t mean to offend your work.

613
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,380
I did not consent to this!

614
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:36,020
Delete it!

615
00:45:36,300 --> 00:45:38,670
I bought these paintings legally.

616
00:45:39,580 --> 00:45:42,020
I can experiment on or do whatever
I want with them.

617
00:45:42,630 --> 00:45:43,380
And one more thing,

618
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,980
the interview is part of your job.

619
00:45:46,260 --> 00:45:47,710
Is asking me to go out with you

620
00:45:49,220 --> 00:45:50,620
part of the job, then?

621
00:45:50,690 --> 00:45:52,410
That has nothing to do with this.
Don’t mix things up.

622
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:53,550
It’s all connected.

623
00:45:54,780 --> 00:45:55,650
Will you delete it or not?

624
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:59,100
I don’t see why I need to.

625
00:46:01,090 --> 00:46:02,010
I quit.

626
00:46:02,610 --> 00:46:03,070
Hey.

627
00:46:03,580 --> 00:46:04,050
Hey.

628
00:46:06,620 --> 00:46:08,340
Are you gonna get emotional
like this every time?

629
00:46:09,030 --> 00:46:09,540
Yes.

630
00:46:09,840 --> 00:46:10,780
So what if I do?

631
00:46:11,460 --> 00:46:12,050
Fine.

632
00:46:13,050 --> 00:46:14,820
I’ll let you go home
and calm down for today.

633
00:46:15,810 --> 00:46:17,540
I know you’ll come back to me.

634
00:46:17,630 --> 00:46:18,420
I won’t.

635
00:46:18,790 --> 00:46:20,190
I’m breaking up with you.

636
00:47:24,410 --> 00:47:25,820
Koh’s AI, Hive Mind,

637
00:47:26,370 --> 00:47:29,420
can we delete the information
that’s been fed to the system?

638
00:47:29,750 --> 00:47:31,260
That’s hard to do.

639
00:47:31,650 --> 00:47:32,380
I can’t sleep.

640
00:47:34,170 --> 00:47:35,180
Come back with me.

641
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:36,860
You’re so selfish.

642
00:47:37,310 --> 00:47:39,900
If you can’t sleep, then that’s
your problem to deal with.

643
00:47:42,840 --> 00:47:44,940
If you’re not coming back to me,

644
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:47,540
I’ll stop.

645
00:47:48,690 --> 00:47:49,620
Let’s end things here.

646
00:47:52,070 --> 00:47:52,900
It’s for the best.
